  <a href="#1" id="1">
   &gt;From behind bars, Nelson Mandela has dominated the fight for black rights in South Africa.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   1944 Mandela joins the African National Congress at age 26, later becoming president of the group's Youth League.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   January, 1962 Attends Pan-African Freedom Movement Conference in Ethiopia; travels to London to meet with leftists.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   July, 1963 With Mandela in jail, police raid ANC offices, seizing documents outlining guerrilla campaign.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   January, 1985 President Pieter W. Botha offers to free Mandela if he renounces violence; Mandela refuses until the government takes steps to dismantle apartheid and grants full political rights to blacks.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   December, 1989 President Frederik W. de Klerk meets Mandela for the first time.
  </a>
